name: Broncos' new uniforms
summary: The Denver Broncos have unveiled their new uniforms for the 2024 season, marking the first significant uniform change in over 25 years. The new uniforms, dubbed the "Mile High Collection," feature elements inspired by Denver's high altitude, the Rocky Mountains, and the team's 1977 Super Bowl victory. The collection includes a navy blue jersey, orange pants, and an alternate helmet with a white base and orange stripes. The uniforms aim to evoke the spirit of the city and the team's history, while also providing a fresh and modern look. The Broncos will debut their new uniforms during the 2024 NFL Draft, which will be held in Denver.
